{"title_page": "Takumi Uesato", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Takumi Uesato\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Takumi Uesato\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1990|4|29}}\n| birth_place = [[Okinawa Prefecture|Okinawa]], [[Japan]]\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| height = {{Height|m=1.74}}\n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub = [[Kaya F.C.\u2013Iloilo|Kaya\u2013Iloilo]]\n| clubnumber = 39\n| youthyears1 = \u2013\n| youthclubs1 = Okinawa Minami\n| youthyears2 = \u2013\n| youthclubs2 = Miyakojima Municipal North M.S.\n| youthyears3 = \u2013\n| youthclubs3 = Miyako H.S.\n| years1 = 2009\u20132011\n| clubs1 = [[Kyoto Sanga FC]]\n| caps1 = 2\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2011\u20132013\n| clubs2 = [[FC Ryukyu]]\n| caps2 = 33\n| goals2 = 4\n| years3 = 2014\u20132016\n| clubs3 = [[USV Allerheiligen|Allerheiligen]]\n| caps3 = 9\n| goals3 = 3\n| years4 = 2016\u20132017\n| clubs4 = [[JP Voltes F.C.|JPV Marikina]]\n| caps4 = 14\n| goals4 = 15\n| years5 = 2018\n| clubs5 = [[Ceres\u2013Negros F.C.|Ceres\u2013Negros]]\n| caps5 = 0\n| goals5 = 2\n| years6 = 2018\n| clubs6 = [[JP Voltes F.C.|JPV Marikina]]\n| caps6 = \n| goals6 = \n| years7 = 2020\u2013\n| clubs7 = [[Kaya F.C.\u2013Iloilo|Kaya\u2013Iloilo]]\n| caps7 = 0\n| goals7 = 0\n| totalcaps = 58\n| totalgoals = 22\n| nationalyears1 = \n| nationalteam1 = \n| nationalcaps1 = \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| manageryears1 = \n| managerclubs1 = \n|medaltemplates=\n{{Medal|Team|[[Kyoto Sanga FC]]}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[Emperor's Cup]]|[[2011 Emperor's Cup|2011]]}}\n| club-update = \n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''Takumi Uesato'''|\u4e0a\u91cc \u7422\u6587|Uesato Takumi|born April 29, 1990 in [[Okinawa Prefecture]], Japan<ref name=kyotosanga>{{cite web|publisher=Kyoto Sanga F.C.|title=Kyoto Sanga F.C. Profile|url=http://www.sanga-fc.jp/club/profile/player27-711/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120330170124/http://www.sanga-fc.jp/club/profile/player27-711/|accessdate=22 November 2017|archive-date=30 March 2012|language=ja}}</ref>}} is a [[Japanese people|Japanese]] [[Association football|football]] player who currently plays for [[Kaya F.C.\u2013Iloilo|Kaya\u2013Iloilo]] of the [[Philippines Football League]].\n\n==Career==\nIn his youth, Uesato played for Okinawa Minami FC. He was also part of his schools' football team playing for Miyakojima Municipal North Middle School and Miyako High School before playing professionally for [[Kyoto Sanga FC]].\n<ref name=kyotosanga/> He made his debut in [[J. League Division 1]] with Kyoto Sanga in 2009.<ref name=\"jleague\">{{cite web|title=Takumi Uesato|url=https://data.j-league.or.jp/SFIX04/?player_id=10307|website=J. League Data Site|accessdate=22 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nAfter his Kyoto Sanga stint, he played for [[FC Ryukyu]] and later for Austrian club [[USV Allerheiligen]]. He then move to the Philippines to play for [[JP Voltes F.C.|JPV Marikina]] at the [[United Football League (Philippines)|United Football League]] and later, the [[Philippines Football League]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Takumi Uesato <nowiki>|</nowiki> JPV Marikina FC|url=http://en.jp-voltes.org/player/uesato-takumi/|publisher=JPV Marikina FC|accessdate=22 November 2017}}</ref> In January 2018, he moved to [[Ceres\u2013Negros F.C.|Ceres\u2013Negros]]<ref>{{cite news|title=TAKUMI UESATO JOINS CERES-NEGROS|url=http://ceresfootball.com/takumi-uesato-joins-ceres-negros/|accessdate=4 January 2018|publisher=Ceres-Negros FC|date=4 January 2018}}</ref> and left the club in July 2018.<ref name=\"ceresletsgo\">{{cite news |last1=Co |first1=Adrian Stewart |title=Ceres lets Uesato go, gets 5 new players |url=https://www.panaynews.net/ceres-lets-uesato-go-gets-5-new-players/ |accessdate=19 July 2018 |work=Panay News |date=19 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Club statistics==\n<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/players/takumi-uesato/74694/ Japan - Takumi Uesato - Profile with news, career statistics and history - Soccerway]</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[Emperor's Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[J. League Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Kyoto Sanga FC]]\n|[[2009 J. League Division 1|2009]]\n|2||0||0||0||0||0||2||0\n|-\n|[[2010 J. League Division 1|2010]]\n|0||0||0||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|[[2011 J. League Division 2|2011]]\n|0||0|| || ||colspan=\"2\"|-||0||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Career total\n!2||0||0||0||0||0||2||0\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{J.League player|10307}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Uesato, Takumi}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football people from Okinawa Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Japanese footballers]]\n[[Category:J1 League players]]\n[[Category:J2 League players]]\n[[Category:Japan Football League players]]\n[[Category:Kyoto Sanga FC]]\n[[Category:FC Ryukyu players]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriate sportspeople in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:JPV Marikina F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Ceres\u2013Negros F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n\n\n{{Japan-footy-forward-1990s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Takumi Uesato\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Takumi Uesato\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1990|4|29}}\n| birth_place = [[Okinawa Prefecture|Okinawa]], [[Japan]]\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| height = {{Height|m=1.74}}\n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub = [[Kaya F.C.\u2013Iloilo|Kaya\u2013Iloilo]]\n| clubnumber = 39\n| youthyears1 = \u2013\n| youthclubs1 = Okinawa Minami\n| youthyears2 = \u2013\n| youthclubs2 = Miyakojima Municipal North M.S.\n| youthyears3 = \u2013\n| youthcl