eb|title=Takumi Uesato|url=https://data.j-league.or.jp/SFIX04/?player_id=10307|website=J. League Data Site|accessdate=22 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nAfter his Kyoto Sanga stint, he played for [[FC Ryukyu]] and later for Austrian club [[USV Allerheiligen]]. He then move to the Philippines to play for [[JP Voltes F.C.|JPV Marikina]] at the [[United Football League (Philippines)|United Football League]] and later, the [[Philippines Football League]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Takumi Uesato <nowiki>|</nowiki> JPV Marikina FC|url=http://en.jp-voltes.org/player/uesato-takumi/|publisher=JPV Marikina FC|accessdate=22 November 2017}}</ref> In January 2018, he moved to [[Ceres\u2013Negros F.C.|Ceres\u2013Negros]]<ref>{{cite news|title=TAKUMI UESATO JOINS CERES-NEGROS|url=http://ceresfootball.com/takumi-uesato-joins-ceres-negros/|accessdate=4 January 2018|publisher=Ceres-Negros FC|date=4 January 2018}}</ref> and left the club in July 2018.<ref name=\"ceresletsgo\">{{cite news |last1=Co |first1=Adrian Stewart |title=Ceres lets Uesato go, gets 5 new players |url=https://www.panaynews.net/ceres-lets-uesato-go-gets-5-new-players/ |accessdate=19 July 2018 |work=Panay News |date=19 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Club statistics==\n<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/players/takumi-uesato/74694/ Japan - Takumi Uesato - Profile with news, career statistics and history - Soccerway]</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[Emperor's Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[J. League Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Kyoto Sanga FC]]\n|[[2009 J. League Division 1|2009]]\n|2||0||0||0||0||0||2||0\n|-\n|[[2010 J. League Division 1|2010]]\n|0||0||0||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|[[2011 J. League Division 2|2011]]\n|0||0|| || ||colspan=\"2\"|-||0||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Career total\n!2||0||0||0||0||0||2||0\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}