ague Data Site]{{in lang|ja}}</ref> He plays for Japanese club [[Vegalta Sendai]] on loan from the Russian club [[PFC CSKA Moscow]].\n\n==Club career==\nOn 31 August 2018, he signed a 4-year contract with the [[Russian Premier League]] club [[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[PFC CSKA Moscow]]|url=https://pfc-cska.com/novosti/vse-novosti/novosti-osnovy/takuma-nishimura-v-pfk-cska/|title=\u0422\u0430\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0430 \u041d\u0438\u0441\u0438\u043c\u0443\u0440\u0430 \u2014 \u0432 \u041f\u0424\u041a \u0426\u0421\u041a\u0410|trans-title=Takuma Nishimura joins PFC CSKA|date=31 August 2018|language=Russian}}</ref>\n\nHe scored his first Russian Premier League goal for CSKA on 9 March 2019 in a 3\u20130 victory over [[FC Rubin Kazan]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Russian Premier League]]|url=https://premierliga.ru/match/match_12721.html|title=CSKA v Rubin game report|date=9 March 2019|language=Russian}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 January 2020 CSKA announced that he will join Portuguese club [[Portimonense S.C.|Portimonense]] on loan for the rest of the 2019\u201320 season, with a purchase option.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[PFC CSKA Moscow]]|url=https://pfc-cska.com/novosti/vse-novosti/novosti-osnovy/takuma-nishimura-zavershit-sezon-v-portugalii/|title=\u0422\u0430\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0430 \u041d\u0438\u0441\u0438\u043c\u0443\u0440\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0438\u0442 \u0441\u0435\u0437\u043e\u043d \u0432 \u041f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0443\u0433\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0438|date=10 January 2020|language=Russian}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 26 January 2020}}<ref>Nippon Sports Kikaku Publishing inc./\u65e5\u672c\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4\u4f01\u753b\u51fa\u7248\u793e, [https://www.amazon.co.jp/J1-J3%E9%81%B8%E6%89%8B%E5%90%8D%E9%91%91%E3%83%8F%E3%83%B3%E3%83%87%E3%82%A3%E7%89%88-2018-NSK-MOOK/dp/4905411521 \"J1&J2&J3\u9078\u624b\u540d\u9451\u30cf\u30f3\u30c7\u30a3\u7248 2018 (NSK MOOK)\"], 7 February 2018, Japan,